&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>ISO/IEC 18974 Conformance Guide</title><link>https://OpenChain-Project.github.io/OpenChain-KWG/en/guide/iso18974_guide/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://OpenChain-Project.github.io/OpenChain-KWG/en/guide/iso18974_guide/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This guide explains each requirement clause of ISO/IEC 18974 (OpenChain Security Assurance) one by one. It describes what Verification Materials each clause requires, how to comply, and what sample documents can be used immediately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Author : OpenChain Korea Work Group / &lt;a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"&gt;CC BY 4.0&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="target-audience"&gt;Target Audience&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Security managers and open source program managers at organizations establishing an open source security assurance framework for the first time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engineers building open source vulnerability management processes in DevSecOps environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organization staff preparing to add ISO/IEC 18974 certification after obtaining ISO/IEC 5230 certification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="relationship-with-isoiec-5230"&gt;Relationship with ISO/IEC 5230&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert"&gt;&lt;div class="h4 alert-heading" role="heading"&gt;ISO/IEC 18974 adds a security layer on top of ISO/IEC 5230&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ISO/IEC 5230 (License Compliance)&lt;/strong&gt; covers the foundational program for systematically managing open source license obligations.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>31th Meeting</title><link>https://OpenChain-Project.github.io/OpenChain-KWG/en/meeting/2026/31th/</link><pubDate>Tue, 31 Mar 2026 17:23:41 +0900</pubDate><guid>https://OpenChain-Project.github.io/OpenChain-KWG/en/meeting/2026/31th/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="schedule"&gt;Schedule&lt;/h2&gt;
